16:57.750 --> 17:00.639
Mr. Florrick arranged
this task force

17:00.680 --> 17:01.715
in order to then
shake down

17:01.750 --> 17:05.311
the real estate developers
for payoffs?
Yes, sir.

17:05.350 --> 17:08.251
And did you agree
with Mr. Childs' estimation?

17:08.290 --> 17:10.053
My opinion was irrelevant.

17:10.090 --> 17:11.455
I did what I was asked.

17:11.490 --> 17:13.549
By whom?

17:13.600 --> 17:15.090
Excuse me.

17:15.130 --> 17:16.722
You said that you did
what you were asked.

17:16.760 --> 17:18.523
Who were you referring to?

17:18.570 --> 17:20.265
It was a figure of speech.

17:20.300 --> 17:23.235
I understand,
but figures of speech
mean something, so who

17:23.270 --> 17:25.500
asked you to do something:
was it your boss, Mr. Florrick,

17:25.540 --> 17:29.271
or was it Mr. Childs,
your peer?

17:32.480 --> 17:33.845
Mr. Childs.

17:33.880 --> 17:35.814
What did he ask you to do?

17:37.650 --> 17:39.709
He asked me
to keep track of Peter.

17:39.750 --> 17:43.550
He thought he was being
bribed to DP cases.

17:43.590 --> 17:45.285
And so,

17:45.330 --> 17:47.093
how are these cases going now?

17:48.130 --> 17:49.427
Excuse me?

17:49.460 --> 17:52.623
These cases that Mr. Florrick
asked you to drop--

17:52.670 --> 17:53.864
I mean, you must be fervently

17:53.900 --> 17:55.697
pursuing them now
that Peter Florrick

17:55.740 --> 17:58.334
is no longer around
to obstruct them.

17:58.370 --> 17:59.803
No, sir.
My goodness.

17:59.840 --> 18:01.728
What happened to them?

18:04.410 --> 18:06.071
We dropped them.

18:11.820 --> 18:13.378
Your witness.

18:13.420 --> 18:14.717
Thank you, Your Honor.

18:14.760 --> 18:17.820
Uh, actually,
just to be clear,

18:17.860 --> 18:21.626
you are the defendant's
sister-in-law, Mariel?

18:21.660 --> 18:23.423
The defendant who killed
