21:46.970 --> 21:49.666
I am a lavwer.

21:49.700 --> 21:51.759
Do you ever want
to be together again?

21:53.940 --> 21:56.079
Peter...

21:59.610 --> 22:01.111
I've been hurt, deeply.

22:01.150 --> 22:04.415
I imagine
I will heal someday,

22:04.450 --> 22:06.987
but for now...

22:07.020 --> 22:09.614
we need a plan, okay?

22:09.660 --> 22:12.083
Okay.

22:13.130 --> 22:15.451
KALINDA:
The grip is still.

22:15.500 --> 22:17.468
Focus is on the front sight.

22:17.500 --> 22:19.525
Are you steady?

22:19.570 --> 22:20.764
I think so.

22:20.800 --> 22:23.098
Now the hardest
part-- the trigger.

22:23.140 --> 22:25.005
There's a natural
tendency for the muscles

22:25.040 --> 22:27.600
in the hand and wrist to move
in tandem with the fingers.

22:27.640 --> 22:29.005
You need to resist that.

22:29.040 --> 22:30.678
You need to let
your forefinger act

22:30.710 --> 22:32.109
independently, squeezing.

22:32.150 --> 22:33.947
Do you
understand?

22:33.980 --> 22:34.878
I think so.

22:34.920 --> 22:38.788
And so, with almost
no pressure at all,

22:38.820 --> 22:41.152
concentrate on the center
of your target.

22:41.190 --> 22:43.454
