23:28.140 --> 23:30.438
Nice.

23:30.470 --> 23:33.928
Raise your arm
and try again.

23:38.250 --> 23:41.640
So, um, as I was saying,
Mr. Sweeney,

23:41.680 --> 23:46.185
there was blood and skin found
on a rope at your house, right?

23:46.220 --> 23:47.653
Yes, that's right.

23:47.690 --> 23:51.126
And, uh, this blood and skin--

23:51.160 --> 23:53.799
the police say
it all matched your wife.

23:53.830 --> 23:55.195
Is that right?

23:55.230 --> 23:57.460
Yes, we like to cut
our own firewood

23:57.500 --> 23:59.127
and wrap the
kindling in rope,

23:59.170 --> 24:01.832
and I believe my
dearest Carolyn

24:01.870 --> 24:04.566
cut herself.

24:04.610 --> 24:06.202
CROZIER:
Yeah, that seems
understandable, I get that.

24:06.240 --> 24:08.174
(sighs)

24:08.210 --> 24:11.771
So, I need to ask you this,
Mr. Sweeney, please excuse me.

24:11.810 --> 24:13.141
Go right ahead, dear.

24:13.180 --> 24:14.875
You never strangled
your wife, right?

24:14.920 --> 24:17.115
(chuckling):
My goodness, no.

24:17.150 --> 24:18.082
Thank God.

24:18.120 --> 24:19.678
(chuckles)

24:19.720 --> 24:22.587
So this, uh...

24:24.190 --> 24:25.555
